## Build and Deployment Commands

The `ryoppippi/dotfiles` repository uses Nix Flakes to define various build and deployment commands as `perSystem.apps` in its `flake.nix` file.  These applications are shell scripts wrapped using `localPkgs.writeShellScript` and can be executed using `nix run .#<app_name>`.  

### `build` App

The `build` app performs a dry run build of the system configuration without applying it.  It uses `nix-output-monitor` to display the build progress. 

```nix
build = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript (if isDarwin then "darwin-build" else "home-manager-build") ''
      set -e
      echo "Building ${if isDarwin then "darwin" else "Home Manager"} configuration..."
      ${localPkgs.nix-output-monitor}/bin/nom build .#${
        if isDarwin then
          "darwinConfigurations.${hostname}.system"
        else
          "homeConfigurations.${username}.activationPackage"
      }
      echo "Build successful! Run 'nix run .#switch' to apply."
    ''
  );
};
``` 

For macOS (`isDarwin` is true), it builds `darwinConfigurations.${hostname}.system`.  For Linux, it builds `homeConfigurations.${username}.activationPackage`. 

### `switch` App

The `switch` app builds and applies the system configuration.  It also uses `nix-output-monitor` and clears the Fish shell cache after applying changes.  

```nix
switch = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript (if isDarwin then "darwin-switch" else "home-manager-switch") ''
      set -eo pipefail
      echo "Building and switching to ${if isDarwin then "darwin" else "Home Manager"} configuration..."
      ${
        if isDarwin then
          "sudo nix run nix-darwin -- switch --flake .#${hostname} |& ${localPkgs.nix-output-monitor}/bin/nom"
        else
          "nix run nixpkgs#home-manager -- switch --flake .#${username} |& ${localPkgs.nix-output-monitor}/bin/nom"
      }
      echo "Clearing fish cache..."
      rm -rf "$TMPDIR/fish-cache"
      echo "Done!"
    ''
  );
};
``` 

On macOS, it executes `sudo nix run nix-darwin -- switch --flake .#${hostname}`.  On Linux, it runs `nix run nixpkgs#home-manager -- switch --flake .#${username}`. 

### `update` App

The `update` app updates all flake inputs by running `nix flake update`. 

```nix
update = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript "flake-update" ''
      set -e
      echo "Updating flake.lock..."
      nix flake update
      echo "Done! Run 'nix run .#switch' to apply changes."
    ''
  );
};
``` 

### `fmt` App

The `fmt` app formats code using `treefmt`.  It executes the `treefmt` wrapper provided by the `treefmt-nix` flake module. 

```nix
fmt = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript "treefmt-wrapper" ''
      exec ${config.treefmt.build.wrapper}/bin/treefmt "$@"
    ''
  );
};
``` 

### Other Defined Apps

#### `nvim-restore` App

This app restores Neovim plugins.  It executes a bash script located at `nix/modules/home/programs/neovim/check.sh` to manage Neovim's lazy plugins. 

```nix
nvim-restore = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript "nvim-restore" ''
      : "''${DOTFILES_DIR:=${homedir}/ghq/github.com/ryoppippi/dotfiles}"
      if [ ! -d "$DOTFILES_DIR" ]; then
        DOTFILES_DIR="$(pwd)"
      fi
      exec ${localPkgs.bash}/bin/bash \
        ${./nix/modules/home/programs/neovim/check.sh} \
        "$DOTFILES_DIR/nvim" \
        "$HOME/.local/share/nvim/lazy" \
        ${localPkgs.neovim}/bin/nvim
    ''
  );
};
``` 

#### `update-ai-tools` App

This app specifically updates the `llm-agents` flake input. 

```nix
update-ai-tools = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript "update-ai-tools" ''
      set -e
      echo "Updating AI tools inputs..."
      nix flake update llm-agents
      echo "Done! Run 'nix run .#switch' to apply changes."
    ''
  );
};
``` 

#### `update-node-packages` App

This app updates Node.js package definitions by executing a bash script. 

```nix
update-node-packages = {
  type = "app";
  program = toString (
    localPkgs.writeShellScript "update-node-packages" ''
      set -e
      exec ${localPkgs.bash}/bin/bash nix/packages/node/update.sh "$@"
    ''
  );
