{"result":"Git hooks, specifically pre-commit hooks, are configured in your Nix Flakes setup using the `git-hooks.nix` flake input and integrated via `flake-parts` modules . The configuration involves defining the `git-hooks` input, importing its `flakeModule`, setting up the `perSystem.pre-commit` options, and installing the hooks in `devShells.default` . Additionally, there's a separate Home Manager module that installs other git hooks, including a `pre-commit` hook for `treefmt` .

## Git Hooks Configuration Details

### `git-hooks` Input
The `git-hooks` input is defined in your `flake.nix` file . The input URL for `git-hooks` is `github:cachix/git-hooks.nix` .

```nix
    git-hooks = {
      url = "github:cachix/git-hooks.nix";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
```


This input is then passed to the `outputs` section of your `flake.nix` .

### `flakeModule` Import
The `git-hooks` flake module is imported within the `flake-parts.lib.mkFlake` call in `flake.nix` .

```nix
      imports = [
        treefmt-nix.flakeModule
        git-hooks.flakeModule
      ];
```


This import makes the `pre-commit` options available for configuration within the `perSystem` section.

### `perSystem` Pre-commit Configuration
The `perSystem.pre-commit` configuration defines which hooks are enabled and their associated packages .

```nix
          # Git hooks configuration
          pre-commit = {
            check.enable = false;
            settings.hooks = {
              treefmt = {
                enable = true;
                package = config.treefmt.build.wrapper;
              };
              deadnix.enable = true;
              statix.enable = true;
            };
          };
```


In this configuration, `treefmt`, `deadnix`, and `statix` are enabled as pre-commit hooks. The `treefmt` hook uses the `config.treefmt.build.wrapper` package .

### `devShells.default` Installation
The git hooks are installed into the default development shell (`devShells.default`) using the `config.pre-commit.installationScript` .

```nix
          # DevShell with pre-commit hooks
          devShells.default = localPkgs.mkShell {
            shellHook = ''
              ${config.pre-commit.installationScript}
            '';
          };
```


This `shellHook` ensures that when you enter the development shell, the configured git hooks are installed in your local Git repository.

### Home Manager Git Hooks
In addition to the `git-hooks.nix` flake, there's a Home Manager module at `nix/modules/home/git-hooks.nix` that defines other git hooks . This module installs a `pre-commit` hook that runs `nix run .#fmt` (which is the `treefmt` wrapper) on staged files . It also installs `post-commit`, `post-checkout`, `post-merge`, and `post-rewrite` hooks that automatically run `nix run .#switch` if Nix configuration files (like `flake.nix` or `flake.lock`) have changed .

This Home Manager module is imported in `nix/modules/home/default.nix` .

## Notes
